:: Which goes toward what [[User:Bunchofgrapes|Bunchofgrapes]] was saying about bad RfCs. I would never advocate a bad request get through just because others have. I just expected if it was a bad request an uninvolved administrator would say so. By [[User:Bishonen|Bishonen]] deleting it and essentially saying "I told you not to because not enough of an attempt was made to resolve the dispute" without suggesting how to make attempts or pointing out previous RfCs with attempts [[User:Bishonen|Bishonen]] thought were more worthy, I'm back where I started without a real explanation (by real I mean details about WHY the attempts don't work for [[User:Bishonen|Bishonen]]. I honestly don't mean to disrespect [[User:Bishonen|Bishonen]], but saying the arguments are "no good" leaves the reason open to interpretation.  [[User:Anynobody|Anynobody]] 03:14, 12 March 2007 (UTC)

