== [[User:Virgil Vaduva]] ==

This is a <i>seemingly</i> blatant meatpuppet/sockpuppet case. I'm a bit loathe to wade in the middle, as I have been acting as a neutral party, but it <i>appears</i> to be a fairly obvious case. I am not taking a position as to whether this is a meatpuppet or sockpuppet case, as Wikipedia guildelines explicitly treat them equally.

{{user|Virgil Vaduva}} has been very active on [[Brian McLaren]]/[[Talk:Brian McLaren]]. {{user|Frank Thomas}} has very recently joined in the fray. I provided a [[WP:3O|third opinion]] at the posted request of {{user|Will3935}}. I have been intervening since as a fellow editor/informal mediator, trying to cool things down. I have repeatedly asked that they take a breath and focus on the article. Just explaining how I got involved, now to the crux of the matter. 

Frank's contributions are very suspcious. Warning flag #1, checking [[Special:Contributions/Frank_Thomas|his contributions]], you can see his 5th-8th edits show an intimate understanding of Wikipedia that are unusual for a new user.[http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Talk:Preterism&diff=prev&oldid=98431613]
[http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Talk:Preterism&diff=prev&oldid=98502282]
[http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Talk:Preterism&diff=prev&oldid=98908853]
[http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Talk:Preterism&diff=prev&oldid=98959377] Such an early familiarity with Wikipedia rules is one of the primary warning flags for meat/sock-puppetry. Virgil was editing the same article, during the same time period.[http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Preterism&diff=prev&oldid=98295282]
[http://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Preterism&diff=prev&oldid=98320584]
